Female genitalia:
Spermatheca with a strongly sclerotized, spherical nodulus, with a long and strongly curved cornu terminating in a cap-like structure (fig. 
10
). Two pairs of strongly sclerotized bursal sclerites, with sclerotized spines (fig. 
11
).

Distribution: This species is widely distributed in many east Asian countries, such as Malaysia , Indonesia , Philippines , Cambodia , Burma , Myanmar , Thailand , Brunei , Laos , Vietnam , Singapore , northwards to Southern China , westwards to Bangladesh , eastwards to Sulawesi and as far as the Wallace-line (
Fig. 6
).
